Added 3 files to handle source storage function.

Source object will be the primary type for storing source information. Contains the following fields. More can be added as necessary.
1) Source Title (compulsory field)
2) Source Type (compulsory field)
3) Source Details (compulsory field)
4) Source Tags (can contain 0 or more tags)

Functions should be able to accomplish the following:
1) Add a new source to the database of sources
2) Delete sources from the database by index
3) Mass delete all sources from the database
4) Load existing database from an external txt file
5) Write current database to external txt file
6) Edit the each of the parameters in each source individually and by index

commitResults.messageTitle: Massive update for complete implementation of the pin function
commitResults.messageBody:
Users can now pin sources with "pin INDEX" and unpin it with "unpin INDEX"

Control systems in place to prevent pinning of pinned sources and unpinning of unpinned sources

Pinning a source immediately brings it to the top and unpinning a source brings it to the first position of an unpinned source

Users are not allows to order pinned sources or move sources to the positions of pinned sources

The pinned sources are persistent in that they will be saved every time a command affecting them is made

Pinning and unpinning is not an undoable command and so does not interact with the undo or redo commands

Minor modifications to ModelManager to account for these new changes

Minor modifications to CustomOrder and Delete to account for this new function

Updates to user guide, developer guide and tests for new fuction are still pending for now
